(Deluxe Taxi)

00:51:11.375 --> 00:51:14.485
- That'll be 88 dollars. - What? Why is it so expensive?

00:51:15.585 --> 00:51:16.985
It's a deluxe taxi.

00:51:17.685 --> 00:51:20.685
Darn it. If only I'd known before hailing it.

00:51:21.685 --> 00:51:22.725
Here.

00:51:25.825 --> 00:51:26.995
Your change.

00:51:31.965 --> 00:51:34.605
This just looks like an ordinary funeral home.

00:51:34.835 --> 00:51:36.605
So he really came to pay his respects?

00:51:36.905 --> 00:51:39.844
Bringing a wad of cash like that...

00:51:39.845 --> 00:51:41.775
This can't be a normal funeral home.

00:51:42.975 --> 00:51:46.585
But why are there so many dusty cars at a funeral home?

00:51:46.785 --> 00:51:49.755
(Funeral Hall)

00:51:52.385 --> 00:51:55.555
(Condolence Money Envelope)

00:52:01.965 --> 00:52:02.965
(We ask those without a death notice...)

00:52:03.025 --> 00:52:04.035
(to refrain from paying respects.)

00:52:24.885 --> 00:52:27.185
- I'm here to pay my respects. - You're in the wrong place.

00:52:36.935 --> 00:52:39.734
What? But he didn't even say who he was here to see.

00:52:39.735 --> 00:52:41.835
How could he be in the wrong place? What's going on?

00:52:49.575 --> 00:52:51.815
They seem to be guarding the entrance, not the memorial.

00:52:52.115 --> 00:52:55.345
Why is the chief mourner at the door instead of staying with the altar?

00:52:55.445 --> 00:52:57.085
What a strange funeral home.

00:52:57.615 --> 00:52:58.815
Should we go and give you a hand?

00:52:59.925 --> 00:53:00.985
It's okay.

00:53:02.085 --> 00:53:03.225
You've already helped.

00:53:06.595 --> 00:53:07.995
(Deluxe Taxi)

00:53:25.345 --> 00:53:27.945
Is this thing ever going to get to the top?

00:53:31.085 --> 00:53:32.415
Is it even moving?

00:53:32.855 --> 00:53:34.425
Was it always this slow?

00:53:35.155 --> 00:53:36.725
I don't think it's broken, though.

00:53:37.155 --> 00:53:38.855
It'd better not be.

00:53:39.195 --> 00:53:42.194
Driver Kim, just relax for now and listen to music.

00:53:42.195 --> 00:53:43.535
You'll have a visual soon.

00:53:46.265 --> 00:53:49.135
Gyeong Gu, I think it's a little too low.

00:53:49.165 --> 00:53:51.834
- It's going to be a tight squeeze. - It can't be.

00:53:51.835 --> 00:53:53.545
Go Eun's watching.

00:53:53.705 --> 00:53:57.045
Should I tell them to come down? It looks like a tight squeeze.

00:54:11.925 --> 00:54:13.465
So it was a gambling den after all.

00:54:14.165 --> 00:54:15.295
I fold.

00:54:16.695 --> 00:54:19.435
- A hundred dollars? You won fast. - I'll see your 50...

00:54:20.165 --> 00:54:24.435
- and raise 100. - They decorated with funeral items.

00:54:25.105 --> 00:54:26.335
Unbelievable.

00:54:26.475 --> 00:54:29.205
They sure put a lot of effort into hiding this place.

00:54:29.475 --> 00:54:31.275
Even the police wouldn't suspect a thing.

00:54:31.415 --> 00:54:34.115
Who'd think to put a gambling den inside a funeral home?

00:54:35.885 --> 00:54:37.085
So does that mean those cars...

00:54:37.315 --> 00:54:39.585
are collateral for gambling debts?

00:54:41.385 --> 00:54:43.925
I checked Im Dong Hyeon's finances.

00:54:44.055 --> 00:54:45.294
Right after he got out of prison,

00:54:45.295 --> 00:54:47.365
he acquired a studio apartment in his name.

00:54:48.095 --> 00:54:49.125
A studio apartment?

00:54:49.495 --> 00:54:52.995
But there's a lien on it now. He borrowed a lot and defaulted.

00:55:00.045 --> 00:55:01.244
You're betting 100 chips?

00:55:01.245 --> 00:55:03.745
My gosh, are you really betting 100 on this?

00:55:03.845 --> 00:55:06.915
What kind of hand do you have to be throwing in 100 chips?

00:55:07.645 --> 00:55:10.785
I guess Mr. Im here is a rich boy, betting so recklessly.

00:55:10.815 --> 00:55:13.955
Cut the chitchat. Are you going to fold or not?

00:55:13.985 --> 00:55:16.955
You can't "die" at a funeral home, can you?

00:55:17.595 --> 00:55:18.595
Call.

00:55:19.855 --> 00:55:22.695
- A pair of sevens. - I have a pair of nines.

00:55:22.765 --> 00:55:24.165
Thank you very much.

00:55:24.895 --> 00:55:25.895
What?

00:55:26.395 --> 00:55:28.505
What if Im Dong Hyeon went to prison...

00:55:29.205 --> 00:55:31.735
for the purpose of covering up another truth?

00:55:32.535 --> 00:55:35.045
- Another truth? - On that day, 15 years ago,

00:55:36.105 --> 00:55:38.645
Im Dong Hyeon wasn't in the locker room alone.

00:55:40.015 --> 00:55:42.985
Then the studio he suddenly acquired could have been his payment.

00:55:43.355 --> 00:55:44.415
As for that answer,

00:55:45.115 --> 00:55:46.825
we'll have to get it from Im Dong Hyeon himself.

00:55:47.425 --> 00:55:49.155
I doubt he'll talk easily.

00:55:50.155 --> 00:55:51.655
But he will for Park Min Ho.

00:55:52.395 --> 00:55:53.965
What? Park Min Ho?

00:55:54.425 --> 00:55:59.395
Let's see how Im Dong Hyeon reacts to Park Min Ho.

00:56:01.365 --> 00:56:02.735
Whether he'll be happy to see him...

00:56:03.975 --> 00:56:05.105
or unsettled.

00:56:09.705 --> 00:56:12.875
I got my car back, but I've got nothing left. Darn it.

00:56:17.355 --> 00:56:18.355
What's this?

00:56:19.385 --> 00:56:20.655
What is this thing?

00:56:21.825 --> 00:56:24.525
Long time no see, old friend. How have you been?

00:56:37.805 --> 00:56:39.805
(Shed the Fat, Special Discount for Cash Payments)

00:56:41.905 --> 00:56:44.045
- Hello, Mr. Im. - Get these ready in advance.

00:56:44.115 --> 00:56:46.075
- Let me get that. - No, I've got it.

00:56:46.145 --> 00:56:49.185
- Okay. - Sir, you had a phone call earlier.

00:56:49.245 --> 00:56:51.255
- About four times. - Who was it?

00:56:51.285 --> 00:56:54.155
He said he was a friend of yours. The name was Park Min Ho.

00:56:55.585 --> 00:56:59.125
- Who? - Park Min Ho. He spelled it out.

00:56:59.925 --> 00:57:01.065
What did he say?

00:57:01.865 --> 00:57:03.195
He said he'd call back.

00:57:05.435 --> 00:57:06.595
Okay, got it.

00:57:17.815 --> 00:57:20.815
Seong Uk, that jerk never picks up when I call.

00:57:22.215 --> 00:57:24.355
He only calls when he feels like it. Darn it.

00:57:28.285 --> 00:57:29.685
Park Min Ho.

00:57:32.795 --> 00:57:34.625
This really ticks me off.

00:57:36.795 --> 00:57:39.395
There's no way.

00:57:43.365 --> 00:57:45.375
Why is it so high? Darn.

00:57:49.005 --> 00:57:51.575
Are these jerks messing with me with flyers?

00:57:57.515 --> 00:57:58.585
But are you okay?

00:57:58.985 --> 00:58:00.485
You said you did everything.

00:58:01.055 --> 00:58:02.125
Are you really okay?

00:58:02.455 --> 00:58:03.755
Who on earth is it?

00:58:04.525 --> 00:58:06.225
Who is messing with me?

00:58:09.465 --> 00:58:11.635
- Are you heading out again? - No.

00:58:12.335 --> 00:58:14.435
- Are you looking for something? - No, just get back to work.

00:58:23.245 --> 00:58:24.315
What is this?

00:58:25.775 --> 00:58:28.715
(Spin Class Special: 100 dollars)

